2 — Core concepts & business model

Nodes / Miners = machines (cloud/edge/robots) that run official simulation jobs.

Simulation Job = deterministic parametric Gazebo/ROS2 scenario (world + robot model + veil batch + random seed + config).

Proof-of-Simulation (PoSim) = cryptographic proof that (a) a particular job ran on some compute, (b) produced deterministic outputs matching a signed Merkle root of checkpointed outputs, and (c) passed validator checks (metrics within baseline thresholds, safety no-fail). Successful validation → token reward.

Validators = independent nodes or distributed verifiers that recompute/verify a compressed sample (or run lightweight replay) and attest. Could be permissioned at first.

Marketplace = users can buy simulation credits, request custom scenarios, or bid for compute.

Incentives = tokens awarded for validated runs; reputation and stake for validators; slashing for dishonest claims.



