5 — Verification strategy (cheap + secure)

Random checkpoint sampling: Verifiers request Merkle path for randomly selected checkpoint indices; worker provides the checkpoint and proof. Validator recomputes hash and compares to Merkle root.

Light replay: Validator runs short replay of N steps (e.g., 10% of job duration) using job spec + seed and compares deterministic outputs — much cheaper than full run.

Metric cross-check: Check final metric vector against baseline thresholds; if too different → reject.

Statistical validators: Over time, automatically compute deviation distributions and flag anomalous workers.

Third-party audits: Allow trusted auditors to run full replays occasionally and publish findings.



