## Summary (one line)

Require 3 independent device-nodes (geo-separated, sensor-diverse, staked, attesting) to validate a simulation run using Merkle proofs + telemetry cross-checks + deterministic light replays → accepted claim → reward; misbehavior triggers slashing and reputation loss.

## Goals

1. Prevent gaming/fraud (fake claims, collusion, replay attacks).


2. Ensure validators are physically distinct devices with telemetry and location attestations.


3. Make verification economically costly to cheat (stake + slashing).


4. Keep verification practical (random checkpoint sampling + light replays).


5. Provide an auditable, cryptographically verifiable trail.




