## Telemetry cross-check algorithm (practical)

Validators compare time-series statistics (not raw sensor streams to protect privacy) to detect fabrication:

1. Hash-window: Worker publishes H(window_blob) for each sample window. Validators ask for window_blob for sampled windows only.


2. Cross correlation: For IMU/accelerometer data, compute cross-correlation between worker’s claimed motion and validator’s local estimation (if validator has sensors observing same robot) OR compare global invariants (energy, mean, variance).


3. Consistency tests:

Device movement integrals must match position differences implied by joint states and kinematics within epsilon.

Camera-based visual odometry vs IMU-integrated pose must be consistent.



4. Outlier detection: Run anomaly detection on signature features (FFT energy, spectral spikes) — abrupt, unnatural regularities indicate synthetic data.



If telemetry cannot be meaningfully cross-checked (e.g., validator remote, no line-of-sight), validator should fall back to deterministic checkpoint & replay verification — but quorum rules should require at least one validator that can check telemetry modality.


